HEADWORD: Jollification
<hw>Jol`li*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Jolly</ets> + L. <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make. See
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>A merrymaking; noisy festivity.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We have had a <qex>jollification</qex> or so together.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jollily</ent>⟦br⟧
